<!--STACKS PLUS
	Feature: 	Simplified stack sizes that keeps close to vanilla experience.
				Bundles and consumables stack to 50
				Ammo stacks to 500
				Resources are generally 500, 1000, or 6000
				Gas, Coins, and plant fibers stack to 30000
				Placeable blocks (like workstations) to 500
				Farming and General blocks to 5000
				Opening bundles adapted to new stack sizes
				
	Default: 	Default values are listed next to each line of code.
	
	XML's: 		Items, Blocks, Recipes, Localization
	
	Why: 		Quality of Life, improve the vanilla experience
				Stack sizes more consistent with each other.
				Easier to remember and organize.
				Took HEAVY consideration of economic impact utilizing complex excel formulas.
				This section could be simplified, but made it possible for others to make specific adjustments.
	
	Delete?: 	Only modifies existing items, therefore safe to remove from existing games.
				After removing from existing games, existing stacks will stay that amount until player adjusts them.
					Auto-sort fixes all of them as well.
	
	Code:		Set new "Stacknumber" values by general category and use of each item.
				Updated bundle's "Create_item_count" to match the new stack sizes.
				Made some items unsellable with SellableToTrader="false"
				Code wise, this could be done in significantly less lines, 
					but this shows specifically the changes I made and aided thorough testing.
				Many match the default value, these resulted in thorough testing.-->
				
